{"cursor":"10946","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nAn 'encyclical' was originally a circular letter sent to all the churches of a\nparticular area in the ancient Catholic Church. At that time, the word could be\nused for a letter sent out by any bishop. The word comes from Latin encyclicus\n(from the Greek en kykloi) meaning \"general\" or \"encircling\", which is also the\norigin of the word \"encyclopedia\".\n\nThe term has been used by Catholics, Anglicans and the Eastern Orthodox.\n","linknr":309,"url":"Encyclical","recorded":1362569962,"links":43,"instances":["pamphlet","catholicism"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Papal encyclicals|","Christian genres"],"headings":["Catholic usage","Anglican usage","Important Eastern Orthodox encyclicals","External links","Source","Quotes"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Wikisource-logo.svg/38px-Wikisource-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["flyer","pamphlet"],["cardinal","catholicism"]],"members":["flyer","cardinal"],"related":["Flyer_(pamphlet)","Bishop","Latin","Ancient_Greek","Encyclopedia","Anglican","Eastern_Orthodox","Pope","Papal_brief","Papal_bull","Opening_sentence","Incipit","Catholicism","Apostolic_Constitution","Apostolic_Exhortation","Pope_Pius_XII","Papal_infallibility","Papal","Apostolic_constitution","Papal_bull","Apostolic_letter","Speech","Birth_control","Contraception","Pope_Pius_XI","Casti_Connubii","Pope_Pius_XII","Midwive","Medical","Pope_Paul_VI","Humanae_Vitae","War","Peace","Soviet_Union","Hungary","Hungarian_Revolution_of_1956","Datis_Nuperrime","Sertum_Laetitiae","Luctuosissimi_Eventus","Pope_Paul_VI","Vietnam","Pope_John_Paul_II","Iraq","Pope_Leo_X